Author: Devnetwork
Title: [ANN] Devnetwork - The 1st Decentralized Tech Professional Platform
Body: Website | Whitepaper | Existing Product  Devnetwork creates global professional network, HR tool, community engagement, event management and large-scale professional database. Devnetwork is building on top of Devcamp platform which let every stakeholder in tech industries grow ecosystem together.  In the technology sector where the lack of talent supply is more than 40% and in the fintech and Blockchain industry where more than 70% of the employers are having trouble filling the positions, this creates the opportunity for $600 Billion in HR market in 2017. Devnetwork is blockchain platform on ERC-20 that will revolutionize HR and bring more talents to the industries with long term sustainable solution to mitigate the problem of tech ecosystem.  Devnetwork (dev.wi.th/ico) has tools to create talents hub and analyst for talent‘s profile and also tools for technology companies to hiring and outsourcing the project. Devnetwork works as the blockchain platform for Human Resource Management to be used as a secure form of payment for the hiring of salarymen, freelancers and value-added products. Devnetwork will create escrow and smart contract and receive platform fee from stakeholder and company’s activities in the platform for example, job searching, job post for companies, premium Artificial Intelligence for the suggestion on hiring talents, and more ecosystem features like community and event system.  DEV Token Hard Cap : $ 30M ( Presales $ 10 M ) Soft Cap : $ 3M ICO Tier 1: Feb 16-28, 1 DEV = $0.1215 (12% Bonus) ICO Tier 2: Feb 1-15, 1 DEV = $0.1294 (5.4% Bonus) ICO Tier 3: Mar 16-30, 1 DEV = $0.1364 (0% Bonus) Due to price fluctuations in the crypto market, the token price is based on USD. Exact prices in ETH, BTC, LTC, XLM will be announced on the first day of each tier and stay constant for the entire period the tier. Title: [ANN] Devnetwork - The 1st Decentralized Tech Professional Platform
Body: There are already a large number of hiring systems. The problem is that the information that is entered into the questionnaires in most cases is not checked. At the heart of the system should be not technology, and expertise, and the level of trust of employers should be at the highest level. Only then will the project succeed.

Author: krymson
Title: [ANN] Devnetwork - The 1st Decentralized Tech Professional Platform
Body: This is a very cool project, you guys are creating a decentralized tech job marketplace and ecosystem, but its not very clear at first glance.  On a technical level you guys are ahead of 99% of the projects out there, and you even have a working product that people are using, but its hard to tell what you guys are doing without spending a few minutes reading technical information.  I think it's a good project and I've listed you guys on my ICO review site, but I highly recommend working on the marketing and your copywriting.
